caption:
b"Happy weekend! :smiling_face_with_smiling_eyes: What are you looking forward to doing?

A home library inspires you to search for knowledge or to vicariously live through others' eyes. A craft room reminds you of your potential to create something out of nothing. Our homes reflect what we enjoy. Find the space to do what you love!

Credit :camera:: @jennareadsbooks"

b'Who cleans the dishes most often in your household? Maybe it would be more enjoyable with such a beautiful kitchen? :grinning_face_with_sweat:

This farmhouse apron-front kitchen sink looks gorgeous with the cabinetry! Many people enjoy the large single bowl while others prefer having two bowls. Some kitchen sinks even have three bowls! :winking_face: Find whatever makes this tedious task easier for you.

Credit :camera:: @simpleofferings'

b'What one word would you use to describe how it feels to get organized? :smiling_face_with_halo:

Get organized for the holidays and enjoy the extra space! Some may not enjoy the process, but the feeling afterwards is fantastic!

Credit :camera:: @ourcoffeyhouse

#closetorganization #closetgoals #closetdesign #minimalism #minimalistdecor #homeorganization #organization #homegoals #storage #declutter #myextraspace'

b'What eco-friendly living tips do you have for the home? :recycling_symbol_selector:

Using earth-friendly materials like bamboo, concrete, steel, porcelain, glass, and reclaimed wood in your bathroom can make your space more sustainable! These types of building materials can be incorporated into your bathroom as flooring, recycled tile, and more. The benefits of using recycled goods are endless and can help you reduce costs while also protecting the environment.

Check the link in our bio for more sustainability tips!

Credit :camera:: @intheloftroom'

b'Happy Thanksgiving! :turkey: What are you grateful for?

During such a strange year, it seems especially important to find reasons to be grateful! Help inspire others with your own message of gratitude below. Enjoy the holiday!

Credit :camera:: @inspiredbycharm'

b"What's your favorite color for kitchen cabinets? :thinking_face:

Looking to upgrade your paint color with something eco-friendly? Be sure to use non-toxic paint! Natural paint is made from materials like clay, milk proteins, or citrus, which are solvent-free and have zero levels of volatile organic compounds (VOCs). When deciding on the perfect color, look for GREENGUARD-Certified paint, which helps reduce indoor air pollution and the risk of chemical exposure, making your kitchen remodel more environmentally friendly!

Want more eco-friendly tips for your kitchen? :recycling_symbol_selector: Check the link in our bio!

Credit :camera:: @happyseason.pt"

b"What clutter is most difficult to keep off your kitchen counters? :dizzy_face:

Mail, receipts, car keys, and pens are known to clutter kitchen counters! Organization starts with finding the right space for things, then daily accountability. Is this something you struggle with too?

Also, don't forget that tonight is the last day to enter our Instagram giveaway! :police_car_light: Go to Wednesday's post to enter. Winners will be announced on the same post Monday!

Credit :camera:: @beatriceterrace1903"

b'What do you love most about this cozy outdoor space? :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes:

This lovely setting is from Sarah at @dreamingofhomemaking! Thanks for sharing!

#outdoordesign #outdoordecor #outdoorfurniture #outdoorspace #flowergram #backporch #homegoals #homeorganization #organization #declutter #storage #myextraspace'

b"Are you missing spring/summer yet? :cold_face: Besides dreaming of warmer weather, there's a lot to love about this kitchen photo actually!

The soft pastel colors really compliment the airy feel of the architecture. Plus, look at those gorgeous golden fixtures! Is this what your dream kitchen looks like?

Credit :camera:: @thelondonhomefix"

b"Are you missing spring/summer yet? :cold_face: Besides dreaming of warmer weather, there's a lot to love about this kitchen photo actually!

The soft pastel colors really compliment the airy feel of the architecture. Plus, look at those gorgeous golden fixtures! Is this what your dream kitchen looks like?

Credit :camera:: @thelondonhomefix"

b'Gorgeous skylight in this bathroom! :sun_with_face: What room would you enjoy a skylight in?

Skylights brighten your space naturally, but they have more benefits too! They also provide solar heating and better ventilation, which can help you save money on energy costs.

Credit :camera:: @schultzrealty'

b'What green living tips do you have to share? :green_heart:

For today\xe2\x80\x99s takeover, @ourvanquest shares their eco-friendly upgrades on our Stories. Go take a look! :bus:

Extra Space Storage is ranked as the most green storage company by many sustainability experts. We have over 450 locations with solar panels and growing!

#greenliving #ecofriendly #ecofriendlyproducts #ecofriendlyliving #skoolielife #skoolienation #homegoals #homeorganization #organization #declutter #storage #myextraspace'

Stay tuned for their takeover on our stories this Thursday (11/12)!

#smallspaceliving #skoolieconversion #skoolielife #skoolienation #hiddenstorage #drawer #homegoals #homeorganization #organization #declutter #storage #myextraspace'

b'If you want to display some beautiful plates or colorful spices, would you rather use open-shelving or glass-window cabinets? :thinking_face:

Both are beautiful ways to show off your kitchen pieces! Open shelving provides quick and easy access, but cabinets have timeless appeal. Which would you prefer?

Credit :camera:: @amanda_holstein'

b"What do you love most about changing the furniture? :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes:

Whether you're buying new furniture or repurposing older pieces, furniture can drastically change the feel of a room. Even just moving one couch to a different space can help things to feel fresh again! Rearrange, reorganize, and repurpose pieces to maximize your space.

Credit :camera:: @bestnestliving"

b'What do you love most about this room? :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes::green_heart:

Thanks @dreamingofhomemaking for showing us your beautiful space! 

#laundryroom #laundryroomdecor #laundryroomdesign #mudroommakeover #modernfarmhousedecor #modernfarmhousedesign #homegoals #homeorganization #organization #declutter #storage #myextraspace'

b"Happy Halloween! :jack-o-lantern: Do you decorate for Halloween?

Spooky decor is always fun to celebrate the season! Pumpkins, ghosts, bats, and witches are all such fun characters to place around the home. If you're looking for an activity to do tonight, find some DIY crafts for last-minute Halloween decor!

Credit :camera:: @modernfarmhouseglam"

b"What's your favorite part about Halloween? :ghost:

Pumpkin carving, spooky decor, and tasty fall treats make for such fun traditions! Not to mention dressing up as creative characters, of course! :winking_face: What part are you most excited for?

Credit :camera:: @miss_rusticarrow"

b'Do you prefer bright colors or neutral tones? :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes:

The brilliant orange of this couch brings so much life and energy into this room! It stands in stark contrast to the desert outside. Do you love to use bright colors in your home? Why or why not?

Credit :camera:: @jtreebnb'

b'The days are getting shorter, so soak in as much sun as you can! :sun_with_face:

The preparation for winter has begun and many people are using storage to put away their summer clothes and toys! We often spend more time indoors as the months get colder, so consider what you might do to maximize your space inside.

Credit :camera:: @rockridgecasita'

b"What's one feature you wish your current home had? :thinking_face:

When searching for a new home, make a list of features that matter to you most. How many bedrooms and bathrooms might be obvious, but how do you feel about vaulted ceilings? We hope you find a home you love and we'll keep your items safe while you transition!

Credit :camera:: @hickorygrovecarpentry"

b'What color do you use the most in your home furnishings and decor? :artist_palette:

Adding pops of color can bring excitement or calmness depending on what you decide. Neutral tones are common, but be bold and try new colors occasionally to see what you like! If you like to rotate colors between seasons, use storage to keep off-season items out of the way.

Credit :camera:: @tree_top_chalet'

b'What is it about tiny homes that we love so much? :green_heart:

Whether you live in a small space or not, we all enjoy maximizing the space we have! Small spaces might just require a bit more creativity when it comes to finding room for our many items. Do you love tiny homes because of their creativity?

Credit :camera:: @trottcottage'

b"Do you enjoy more being a guest in someone's home, or having guests in your home? :sleeping_face:

If you're the host try to prepare bedroom essentials like a full set of sheets, including a fitted sheet, top sheet, and a pillowcase along with either a comforter or duvet. Provide bathroom linens like bath towels, hand towels, and washcloths. Store extra linens in a closet so your guests can easily grab one if they need more!

Credit :camera:: @mountnouveau"

b"Fall is here and sometimes we can't help but miss the summer weather! :sun_with_face: What will you miss most about the summer?

As you're bringing in your outdoor furniture to protect against the colder weather, consider using storage to keep it out of your way. Don't lose that precious space in your spare room or garage! We're here to help you make the most of your home.

Credit :camera:: @theriversideretreat"

b'If you could go anywhere on a vacation right now, where would you go? :beach_with_umbrella_selector:

It can be tough social distancing for such long periods of time and wondering when the next vacation will be. We hope everyone is still finding ways to keep things fun at home! Play board games, read books, and make plans for when things get better! Where is your dream vacation destination?

Credit :camera:: @jtreebnb'

b"What's your favorite hobby? :green_heart:

Having the extra space to do what you love is important! Whether that's having a cozy reading nook for exploring other worlds, storage for adventure gear, or a craft room with all your tools. We hope you all are enjoying your weekend and making the most of what it has to offer! 

(:camera:: IG/wildflowerhomeblog)"

b'The wood in this skoolie conversion is so beautiful! :bus: Would you live a life on the road?

The plants are an extra nice piece to help things feel fresh inside the small space. As you maximize the space in your own home, think about spots where you can add greenery.

Credit :camera:: @happyhomebodies'

b'This adorable she shed looks so cozy! :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes: Would you use it for a quiet place to read or something else?

To make it a prime reading nook, install a window for natural light, add lots of shelving to show off your books, and include a comfy couch or oversized chair. Then, grab a blanket and the next book on your reading list! What do you think?

Credit :camera:: @theresa_gromski)'

b'If you could change anything about your bathroom, what would it be? :thinking_face:

Bathroom faucets, handles, towel holders, and rods tend to get rusty and outdated after a while, but you can fix that with a simple bathroom makeover! Opt for modern hardware that adds a decorative touch. Brushed nickel and bronze are popular choices, while black is a new chic trend!

Credit :camera:: @craven_haven'

b'Tiny home style! :green_heart: Who do you know that would love this?

The ladder is not only very functional for a small space, but can also add some rustic or industrial flair. We love the creativity and contrast between light and dark elements!

Credit :camera:: @nicolettenotes'

b"What's the most attractive part about living a minimalist lifestyle? :smiling_face_with_halo:

Living minimally might help you save money, save space, have less clutter, or have a cleaner home. Minimalism can be relaxing, relieving the stress that comes from difficult days. If you're looking to try it out, start by decluttering your home and maximizing your current space.

Credit :camera:: @melb_lifeandhome"

b"This RV renovation looks so cozy! What's your favorite thing about small spaces?

Small space living can be cost-effective, but has other benefits too. Less time spent cleaning certainly sounds attractive! Many people living in small spaces also spend more time enjoying the outdoors. What's your favorite part about small space living?

Credit :camera:: @wholethompsonlife"

b'Do you need this in your backyard? :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes: Check out this garden shed from @themomhack!

Stay tuned for more of Sharee\xe2\x80\x99s garden shed AND she shed this Monday on our stories!

#gardenlife #gardenshed #backyarddesign #diyprojects #sheshed #shesheddesign #homegoals #homeorganization #organization #declutter #storage #myextraspace'

b'Would you rather live in the mountains or on the beach? :mountain_selector::beach_with_umbrella_selector:

Vacationing is a fun way to experience what life would be like if you moved elsewhere. You can also try different sizes of homes through services like AirbnB to find the right amount of space for your lifestyle, like this gorgeous tiny home! :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes: Where would you like to move to?

Credit :camera:: @newfrontiertinyhomes'

b'Which is harder, organizing or designing? :thinking_face:

Pantry organization can make life simpler, but requires a lot of critical thinking. If you want to add some style to the exterior, you can use your design creativity to add a sliding barn door or chalkboard wall! Would you rather do the organizing or designing?

Credit :camera:: @crystal_tara'

b'Do you prefer hardwood or tile floors in your kitchen? :thinking_face:

Upgrading the floor in a room can be a large home renovation project, but will do a lot to change the look. There are many varieties of tile to choose from for different styles, but hardwood floors do have a nice texture. Which do you prefer, tile or hardwood?

Credit :camera:: @fashionablykay'

b'Which room do you spend the most time in? :house_with_garden:

Remodeling your living space to be an open floor plan improves the flow of your home by eliminating unnecessary walls and doorways, making it easier to move around your space and keep the family connected. Plus, this is an often desired feature among home-buyers in case you are selling! Do you prefer an open floor plan or separated rooms?

Credit :camera:: @hestershomestead'

b'What would you use a she shed for? :thinking_face:

Some use she sheds as a creative workspace, others use theirs as a space to relax and unwind. A nice book in a cozy space can release a lot of stress! What would you use a she shed for?

Credit :camera:: @sixat21'

b":police_car_light: Takeover today from @reclaimedkarma on our Stories! :police_car_light: Chris from @reclaimedkarma shows off he and his wife Yvonne's amazing workshop, plus a look at his man cave! Let us know what you think below.

There's a lot of effort that goes into keeping any space tidy. The first step towards organization is careful planning. Think about how to maximize the space in your home, then what tools you'll need to keep things tidy.

Go check out the takeover on our Stories, then let us know what you think below!"

b"What a cozy reading nook! :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes: What's your favorite genre of books?

You want to be able to focus in your reading area, which means the fewer distracting elements, the better. When designing this space, consider adopting a minimalist decorating mindset of \xe2\x80\x9cless is more.\xe2\x80\x9d This doesn\xe2\x80\x99t mean you need to completely abandon personality or pops of color in your nook\xe2\x80\x94just that you should consciously think about what furniture, decor, and styling you want in your space.

Credit :camera:: @breycollective"

b'This inspiring workshop is a 10\xe2\x80\x99x16\xe2\x80\xb2 detached garage that went from "scary, rat infested eyesore" to a "highly efficient inner sanctum". :exploding_head: Do you know someone who would love a space like this?\n\n@LazyGuyDIY became a master of using vertical space to get organized. Planning and execution take a while, but it\'s well worth the effort! Use the link in our bio to see what went into creating this amazing workshop.'

b'Would you rather have vaulted ceilings or more space on your second floor? :thinking_face:

A ceiling makeover can give your home a new modern feel! For a large remodeling project, hire a professional to help you incorporate vaulted ceilings. For something more DIY, consider painting your ceiling an accent color, adding faux beams, or installing ceiling tile.

Credit :camera:: @roehnerryan'

b'Would a man cave in your home be used as an office, a sports room, or a game room? :smiling_face_with_sunglasses:

There are actually many options for a man cave. Check out the link in our bio! No matter what the purpose of the space is, make it your own by adding some fun man cave decor like neon signs, hunting trophies, comic book prints, or sports memorabilia that will inspire you!

Credit :camera:: @kowalskekitchenandbath'

b'Organization in a small space is beyond important! :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes: What are you most impressed by in this beautiful RV?

Shelving, baskets, bins, and other organizational tools can help keep clutter out of the way. Extra Space Storage can help with the larger items or items that you use seasonally. Helping people to a better, more organized, tomorrow is important to us!

Credit :camera:: @laceyautumnbrooke'

b"Do you prefer faux plants or real plants? :herb:

You can't kill a fake plant! For those with a green thumb though, living plants can offer more than just decoration. Both faux and real plants seem to have their pros and cons! Which do you prefer?

Credit :camera:: @construction2style"

b'Would you or your family enjoy a reading nook in the home? :books:

Make sure you have plenty of storage space in or around your book nook! With built-in bookshelves or storage bench drawers, you\xe2\x80\x99ll have a convenient place in your reading corner to set up cute home decor and knick-knacks, as well as store your personal library close to where you\xe2\x80\x99ll be reading.

You can see more photos and read our Reading Nook Design Ideas blog post by tapping the link in our bio. :green_heart: Let us know what you think!

(:camera:: IG/jennifer.johns.129)'

b"If your home had a different decor style, what style would you choose? :couch_and_lamp_selector:

If you'd like to change to a modern minimalist style, look for furniture with bold geometric shapes and clean lines. Opt for a rectangular coffee table with exposed legs. Or incorporate unique shapes and lines with table centerpieces, plant pots, and photo frames.

Credit :camera:: @southwestbysoutheast"

b'Hidden storage underneath the cushions! :green_heart: Which room do you wish you had more space in?

Take advantage of the space under your couch, loveseat, or sofa by adding secret storage drawers! Whether you design a bench-style couch with built-in storage or simply add pullout drawers under an existing couch, this is a great way to store kids toys, board games, DVDs, and more!

Credit :camera:: @nickyhousesnaps'

b"Here's some more kitchen organization! :spoon: Would you prefer a spice drawer or a spice cabinet?

Countertop and wall-mounted spice racks can take up valuable kitchen storage space. Try switching to a spice drawer instead! Just lay the containers flat in a divided drawer for attractive and accessible spice storage.

Credit :camera:: @chelseagthomas"

b"Amazing pantry organization! :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes: Is this what your dream pantry looks like?

With some drywall and shelving, you can turn a kitchen corner into a floor-to-ceiling pantry. If you've felt like you need more space for organization, this could be a great home renovation opportunity.

Credit :camera:: @thedowntownaly"

b'Planning any home renovations currently? :house: One great idea is to add paneling to your walls!

Create a rustic look in your kitchen or bathroom by installing shiplap or wooden planks on walls. Or give bedroom, hallway, and living room walls a makeover with wainscoting, board and batten, or beadboard.

Credit :camera:: @revivalhomedesigns'

b'What do you do with the space under the stairs? :exploding_head: Each of these panels are actually organized drawers that pull out!

Is there another way you would prefer to use the space under your stairs? Depending on the location of the staircase, some use it as a play-space, wine storage, or a pet room! :thinking_face: What would you prefer?

Credit :camera:: @myrestyleproject'

b"What helps you stay focused while working? :laptop_computer:

Having a tidy and organized space for working is important. If you're looking to create a home office with minimal space, try something like this! Keep your chair, computer, keyboard, and other office supplies out of sight with hideaway cabinets and drawers.

Credit :camera:: @nevillejohnsongroup"

b'What do you like most about this tiny home? :house:

Take advantage of vertical space with a lofted bedroom! By building up, you\xe2\x80\x99ll find increased floor space for other living spaces like your kitchen and living room. This can be a good idea for any small home or perhaps a shared kids bedroom.

Credit :camera:: @minttinyhomes'

b"What's the most difficult part of interior design for you? :thinking_face:

You don\xe2\x80\x99t need to worry about decorating your home all at once. Focus on quality of items over quantity when designing with modern furniture and decor. Start small and use each room\xe2\x80\x99s basic features to guide your decorating decisions.

If you have a gorgeous glass-top coffee table, for example, consider using other reflective elements\xe2\x80\x94like mirrors and glazed ceramic vases\xe2\x80\x94around the room to create the theme throughout.

Credit :camera:: @leclairdecor"

b'Would you prefer a spacious laundry room or a space-saving laundry closet? :thinking_face:

You can turn a reach-in closet into a laundry room by removing shelving, putting down a floor protector, and installing the water and drain lines. If the closet is really small, opt for a stackable washer-dryer!

Credit :camera:: @hunted_interior'

b'What room are you most proud of for your interior design? :smiling_face_with_sunglasses:

The barn door on this bathroom adds so much charm! For small space living, this bathroom also makes smart choices to maximize space, such as using a pedestal sink. Which room in your home are you most proud of?

Credit :camera:: @gweenhomedecor'

b"Do you prefer modern or repurposed vintage items? :thinking_face:

One way to add hidden storage to your living room is to use a trunk for a coffee table. Not only does a storage trunk make for a great decorative piece in your living room, but you can also store pillows, blankets, books, and other items inside of it, keeping them out of the way! Is this something you'd like in your home?

Credit :camera:: @ourhomedays"

b"Do you prefer modern or repurposed vintage items? :thinking_face:

One way to add hidden storage to your living room is to use a trunk for a coffee table. Not only does a storage trunk make for a great decorative piece in your living room, but you can also store pillows, blankets, books, and other items inside of it, keeping them out of the way! Is this something you'd like in your home?

Credit :camera:: @ourhomedays"

b'Do you have a favorite piece of functional furniture that helps you organize clutter? :smiling_face_with_halo: What is it?

You could replace a basic coffee table with one that has built-in storage! Hidden coffee table drawers will make it easier to keep remotes, magazines, board games, coasters, and other living room items out of the way.

Credit :camera:: @decormarkethome'

b'Do you know the differences between minimalist and modern interior design? :thinking_face:

See our blog post by tapping the link in our bio! We love to share home tips that can help you get organized and make the most of your space. Which interior design style do you prefer?

Credit :camera:: @bestidblog'

b'What do you like most about this modern bathroom? :green_heart:

Add mirrors throughout your house to add light and create the illusion of extra space. Another good way to improve your home\xe2\x80\x99s lighting is by leaving windows unblocked. Hang simple blinds or shades for privacy and to help regulate temperature, but skip heavier window furnishings like curtains or drapes.

Credit :camera:: @chadmellon'

b'Doing the laundry might be just a bit more enjoyable in a room like this. :winking_face: Do you agree?

With extra cabinets and shelving, the room could serve multiple purposes. Store your pet supplies, cleaning items, coats, and more. What do you think?

Credit :camera:: @smalltownstyleme'

b"We're so excited to reveal all the hard work on this skoolie from @OurVanQuest tomorrow on our stories! :bus: Make sure to come check out their beautiful bus conversion and small space organization tips! Are you as excited as we are? :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes:\n\nAlso, huge congrats on their newborn, Capri!"

b'What feeling best describes a perfectly organized closet? :smiling_face_with_sunglasses:

How would you describe it? Home organization can help reduce stress and anxiety, while making your general day-to-day easier. Decide what things are worth keeping, then find the space to keep them organized!

Credit :camera:: @decluttrme'

b"What's your favorite home organization tip for small space living? :thinking_face:

We've shared some hidden storage blog posts in the link in our bio to help out! A murphy bed like this one is a great idea for maximizing a small space. What tip do you have to share?

Credit :camera:: @lenart_meble"

b"Takeover on our stories today from @themartinnest! :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes: Jessica is showing examples of hidden storage to maximize the space in your home. Her home style is gorgeous and we're excited to share her talent with you!\n\nWhat was your favorite part of the takeover? :green_heart:"

b'Is a mudroom included in your dream home? :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes: Why or why not?

A place to take off your muddy shoes can be nice for helping to keep the rest of your home clean. Plus, a mudroom can serve as a spot to keep jackets, umbrellas, sports equipment, or outdoor gear. More storage area for more home organization! What do you think?

(:camera:: @brunoandlibby)'

b"Do you enjoy painting? Why or why not? :paintbrush_selector::artist_palette:

Painting your cabinets can be an affordable DIY project with a big impact. Be prepared though for some long hours of labor. Some people love painting, others don't! How about you?

Credit :camera:: @sandradeco__sweet_home"

b'On a scale of 1-10, how much do you need this? :grinning_face_with_sweat:

Creative bathroom storage can help keep your counters free of clutter! This useful drawer is just one of the many ideas from our recent blog post on hidden bathroom storage ideas. Let us know what other creative solutions you find for staying organized!

Credit :camera:: @lindyegalloway'

b"What's something you love about your home? :green_heart:

We really love how bright this home is! You can create more light in your home through large windows, but also by painting a room in lighter colors so as to reflect the light. So what do you love about your home?

Credit :camera:: @diariesofmyhome"

b"Takeover on our stories tomorrow w/ @houseofhanesinteriors! Who's excited? :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes:\n\nAshley will be showing the hidden storage in her gorgeous living room. :green_heart: Follow along to see how you can use hidden storage to maximize space and keep things organized in your home!"

b'Gorgeous RV renovation with reclaimed shiplap! :bus: What do you like most about this space?

For any small space, you can use floating shelving to give a more open, airy feel to your home. Hanging plants also leaves more room on your shelves for showing off any books, photos, or trinkets. What do you think?

Credit :camera:: @choosing.less'

b'What do you wish you had more space for? :thinking_face:

Check the link in our bio for some great hidden storage ideas! Using a storage ottoman in the living room is just one way you can maximize the space in your home and keep clutter out of the way.

Credit :camera:: @courtneyungaro_spaceanddesign'

b"Would you rather have a sunroom or home theater? :thinking_face:

Sunrooms are a great home renovation idea if you want a controlled environment where you can enjoy the outdoors while still being inside. On the other hand, doesn't a good movie and some popcorn sound awfully nice? Which would you prefer?

Credit :camera:: @designbykatalin"

b":green_heart: What's your favorite color for a bedroom?

Create a feature wall using a different material or bold paint color! Feature walls add a bit of personality to any room. What color would you choose for a feature wall in your bedroom?

Credit :camera:: @highandtightdesign"

b'Do you prefer a mostly white-painted home or a home with lots of color? :artist_palette:

A quick and easy home improvement project is to paint your walls. Opt for light colors like gray, beige, and white in small rooms to help the space reflect light and feel more open. If you want a more dramatic look in your home, paint with darker colors like navy blue and deep purple. Don\xe2\x80\x99t want to paint the whole room? Accent walls are an easy way to add a pop of color to your space without a ton of work!

Credit :camera:: @nest_twenty_eight'

b'Beautiful butcher block countertops in this RV! :bus: What style countertops are your favorite?

b":police_car_light: Semi-Finals 1 of our home decor bracket challenge! Vote now on our Instagram Story, Facebook poll, and Twitter poll between Modern Farmhouse and Coastal.

Most recognized as the style frequently used by Chip and Joanna Gaines from 'Fixer Upper', modern farmhouse has become one of the most popular home design styles. Combining elements of industrial, rustic, and minimalism, this interior decoration style uses a mix of high and low contrast pieces with a hint of barn-like details to create a home that\xe2\x80\x99s cozy.

Design a relaxing, comfortable environment with the coastal decorating style. This design trend\xe2\x80\x94also called Hamptons style\xe2\x80\x94uses elements inspired by the beach and ocean, featuring plush white sofas, beige woods, shades of blues and greens, and sometimes seashells or ropes.

Who will win? You decide. (:camera:: Modern Farmhouse @jessicadevlindesign, Coastal @caitlinmariedesign)"

b':police_car_light: Round 4 of our home decor bracket challenge! Vote now on our Instagram Story, Facebook poll, and Twitter poll between Eclectic and Traditional.

Eclectic style makes use of many colors, patterns, and decor from multiple eras! While eclectic style decor might look like a hodgepodge, a lot of thought goes into harmonizing the elements of multiple interior decorating styles. One way to do this is to pick out a color scheme, and then build your design around that.

There are no home decor styles quite as classic as traditional style! Homes featuring this trend are geared toward finished wood, rich hues, and fabrics with ornate details like silk and velvet that are rooted in 18th century European and Colonial styles.

Who will win? You decide.

Credit :camera:: Eclectic @lizcaan, Traditional @betweenporches'

b':police_car_light: Round 3 of our home decor bracket challenge! Vote now on our Instagram Story, Facebook poll, and Twitter poll between Vintage/Rustic and Coastal.

Rustic style is a great way to bring the outdoors into your home! It embraces textures and colors that are influenced by nature, as well as organic shapes to help bring warmth to the area. Restore vintage items for that cozy charm!

The relaxing and comfortable coastal style\xe2\x80\x94also called Hamptons style\xe2\x80\x94uses elements inspired by the beach and ocean, featuring plush white sofas, beige woods, shades of blues and greens, and sometimes seashells or ropes.

Whether you\xe2\x80\x99re looking to change up your living room or bedroom, Mid-Century Modern is one of the most versatile decorating styles to use in your home. This retro home design trend is influenced by the 1960s with an emphasis on eccentric patterns, bright colors, molded plastics, and modern furniture.

Bohemian style is an interior decorating trend often associated with free-spirited people, as this style encourages showcasing your individuality with unique color schemes and mismatched furniture. A home that uses boho style decor might include vintage light fixtures, globally-inspired patterned rugs, beaded pillows, and chairs that come in variety of shapes and colors.
